WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.140 --> 00:00:12.620
The TRUBLUE Auto Belay is great for everyone, whether you are new or experienced, child or adult.

00:00:13.220 --> 00:00:19.460
It is important that all users are familiar with the operation of this device before climbing

00:00:19.460 --> 00:00:24.780
Prior to clipping in, all climbers must be instructed in the safe use of the auto belay

00:00:24.900 --> 00:00:31.900
If you have not been trained in the safe operation of the auto belay, please alert the climbing wall staff prior to climbing

00:00:32.760 --> 00:00:38.360
Check auto belay operation by pulling out a short section and allowing it to retract

00:00:38.360 --> 00:00:42.520
Check that the climbing harness is correctly fitted and tightened

00:00:43.560 --> 00:00:50.560
The carabiners open by rotating the gates collar and pushing the gate open towards the center of the carabiner.

00:00:51.640 --> 00:00:57.960
Attach the carabiner to the correct loop on the harness with the latch facing away from the user

00:00:59.400 --> 00:01:04.680
Allow the latch to snap shut, ensuring the collar has rotated back and is locked

00:01:04.680 --> 00:01:09.680
Ensure that no clothing, webbing, or other objects are obstruction the gate or latch

00:01:10.860 --> 00:01:17.860
Check that the carabiner from the auto belay line is connected to the designated loop on the climbing harness and the gate is properly closed

00:01:22.480 --> 00:01:24.960
Double check that the latch is secure

00:01:24.960 --> 00:01:31.280
If the auto belay line fails to retract during climbing, stop climbing immediately and request assistance

00:01:32.080 --> 00:01:35.120
Never climb alongside or above the auto belay

00:01:35.120 --> 00:01:38.100
Never start descent from above the auto belay

00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:44.060
Prior to descent, ensure your descent path and landing are free of people and obstructions

00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:50.720
Always descend feet first using feet to fend off obstacles and prepare for landing

